Crocs, Inc. Key Developments

Crocs, Inc. Appoints Andrew Rees as Class I Director
Jun 7 17
On June 6, 2017, Crocs, Inc. and Blackstone Capital Partners VI L.P. entered into an amendment to the Investment Agreement, dated December 28, 2013, as amended. The Amendment permits the size of the Board of Directors of the company to be increased from eight members to nine members through the company‚Äôs 2018 annual meeting of stockholders. On June 6, 2017, the size of the Board was expanded to nine members and Andrew Rees, the company‚Äôs President and Chief Executive Officer, was appointed to the Board as a Class I director.


Crocs, Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for the Second Quarter of 2017; Revises Earnings Guidance for the Full Year 2017
May 10 17
Crocs, Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company announced revenues of $267,907,000 compared to $279,140,000 for the same period a year ago. Income from operations was $15,582,000 compared to $14,243,000 for the same period a year ago. Income before income taxes was $15,948,000 compared to $13,051,000 for the same period a year ago. Net income was $11,010,000 compared to $10,146,000 for the same period a year ago. Net loss per common share, basic and diluted was $0.08 compared to $0.07 for the same period a year ago. Non-GAAP adjusted net loss attributable to common stockholders was $9,325,000 compared to $6,442,000 for the same period a year ago. Cash used in operating activities was $49,890,000 against $56,938,000 a year ago. Cash paid for purchases of property and equipment was $3,243,000 against $3,216,000 a year ago. 

The company expects second quarter 2017 revenues to be between $305 and $315 million. The Company expects gross margin for the second quarter to be approximately 150 basis points higher than the second quarter of 2016.

The company now expects 2017 revenues to be down low single digits compared to 2016, whereas prior guidance contemplated flat revenues. This change reflects the impact of the agreements outlined above and a further reduction in discount channel sales. The Company continues to expect gross margin for 2017 to be approximately 50%.


Crocs, Inc., Q1 2017 Earnings Call, May 10, 2017
Apr 26 17
Crocs, Inc., Q1 2017 Earnings Call, May 10, 2017


